This paper discusses privacy concerns in geosocial networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a suite of mechanisms for constructing location-centric profiles (LCPs), which involves data aggregation and processing, making it relevant to topics in information retrieval (cs.IR) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the implementation of a public safety application, which involves system design and control (cs.SY) and human-computer interaction (cs.CY). Overall, the paper covers a range of topics that could potentially fall under multiple sub-categories, but the most likely ones are cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.DB, cs.SY, and cs.CY.
